text: Yohani Diloka de Silva, born on July 30, 1993, is a singer, rapper, and YouTuber from Sri Lanka. She started her music journey on YouTube and became famous for her rap cover of "Deviyange Bare." Her singing and rap cover earned her the nickname "Rap Princess" of Sri Lanka. She gained global fame with her cover of "Manike Mage Hithe" and became the first Sri Lankan female singer to get over 3.6 million YouTube subscribers. == References == Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:People from Colombo Category:Sri Lankan Buddhists Category:Bollywood playback singers Category:21st-century singers
